The paper discusses the identification of emerging research topics using bibliometric indicators, which is a common theme in several sub-categories of computer science. However, the focus on bibliometrics and the use of criteria for identifying emerging topics suggest that the paper is most likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper's emphasis on the definition of emergence and the evaluation of the proposed approach suggest that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
